    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.58B1/18</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-11">October 11,
                            1928</date>.<lb/>[Received October 29.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 619</seg>
                    <lb/>
                    <seg rendition="#left">L. of N. No. 1219</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith a
                    communication addressed to you on October 8 by the Secretary General of the
                    League of Nations,<note n="1" xml:id="d228fn1">Not printed.</note> forwarding
                    three copies of the report of the Mixed Committee for the Suppression of
                    Counterfeiting Currency and of the draft Convention drawn up by that
                        Committee,<note n="2" xml:id="d228fn2">League of Nations document
                        C.523.M.181.1927.II.</note> and requesting any observations which the
                    Department may have to make on the proposals contained in the document. The
                    Department will note that Sir Eric<note n="3" xml:id="d228fn3">Sir Eric
                        Drummond, Secretary General of the League of Nations.</note> intends to
                    postpone the general Conference on Counterfeiting Currency if possible until the
                    month of April, 1929, in the hope that the comments of the American Government
                    may previously be received and circulated.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh R. Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
